---
pagination:
    data: intents
    size: 1
    addAllPagesToCollections: true
    alias: intent
permalink: "intents/{{ intent.id }}/"
layout: base.njk
eleventyComputed:
    title: "Web Intents - {{ intent.name }}"
---

{% from "project-status.njk" import projectStatus %}
{% from "we-component.njk" import weCard %}

<div class="plug-detail-header">
    <div class="plug-detail-header-inner">
        <nav class="plug-breadcrumb">
            <a href="/projects/webintents/" class="plug-crumb">Web Intents</a>
            <svg class="plug-crumb-chevron" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 18l6-6-6-6"/></svg>
            <span class="plug-crumb plug-crumb-current">{{ intent.name }}</span>
        </nav>
        <div class="plug-title-row">
            <h1 class="plug-title">{{ intent.name }}</h1>
            <div class="plug-status">
                {{ projectStatus(intent.status) }}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

{#- Dogfood (#2101): 5 of the 6 section-card panels are authored via the `weCard` macro (#2098) — each emits
    an inert `<we-card data-we-spec>` placeholder that the `weComponentSSR` build transform batches through the
    pinned FUI CLI in ONE subprocess for the page and splices to the finished SSR `<article class="fui-card">`,
    byte-identical to the client `<we-card>` CE upgrade, JS-off correct. The panel HEADINGS + intro copy stay
    inside the card body; the dimension/design-system/UX/gaps tables + lists stay PLAIN markup per #1964 (only
    the panel FRAME is a card). The implementing/composing-blocks grid becomes `weCard` tiles following the
    `intentTileSpecs` shape (we:scripts/lib/component-render-build-hook.cjs): card title = block name, body =
    summary + status meter, block type = a header-trailing pill. Its wrapping PANEL frame (and the type pill)
    stay plain, NOT nested `weCard`/`weBadge` — the splice is single-pass; see the inline notes below. -#}
<div class="container block-detail-page">
    <div class="block-body content">
        {{ weCard("", intent.description, "", "section-card") }}

        {% if intent.dimensions %}
        {%- set _dimensionsBody %}
            <h2>Dimensions</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-slate-600">Configurable axes for this intent. Applications declare their chosen value per dimension.</p>
            <table class="data-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Dimension</th>
                        <th>Values</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for key, dim in intent.dimensions %}
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>{{ key }}</code></td>
                        <td>{% for val in dim.values %}<code>{{ val }}</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}</td>
                        <td>{{ dim.description }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
        {% endset -%}
        {{ weCard("", _dimensionsBody, "", "section-card mt-8") }}
        {% endif %}

        {% set implementingBlocks = [] %}
        {% for b in blocks %}
            {% if b.implementsIntent == intent.id or (b.composesIntents and intent.id in b.composesIntents) %}
                {% set _ = implementingBlocks.push(b) %}
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
        {% if implementingBlocks.length %}
        {#- This panel's FRAME stays a plain `.section-card fui-card` (NOT a `weCard`) on purpose: its body
            hosts the block-tile `weCard`s, and the `weComponentSSR` splice is SINGLE-PASS over a page's
            placeholders — a `<we-card>` panel whose `data-we-spec` JSON embeds child `<we-card>` tiles
            double-escapes those children, so they never splice. Nesting `weCard`-in-`weCard` is unsupported
            by this primitive; the substantive dogfood here is the TILE grid (below), so the wrapper is left
            plain and the tiles are the cards. -#}
        <div class="section-card fui-card mt-8">
            <h2>Implementing &amp; Composing Blocks</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-slate-600">Blocks that fulfill this intent directly, or compose it as part of a larger component.</p>
            <div class="standards-grid">
                {% for block in implementingBlocks %}
                {#- Header-trailing type pill. NOTE: this stays the original PLAIN `<span>` pill, NOT a nested
                    `weBadge` — the splice is single-pass, so a `<we-badge>` embedded inside this card's
                    `data-we-spec` JSON is NOT independently rendered (it would leak a raw placeholder into
                    the card's `actionsHtml`). The block TYPE was never a badge component in the source
                    markup either, so a plain pill is faithful. -#}
                {%- set _blockTypePill -%}<span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-gray-100 text-gray-800" style="white-space: nowrap;">{{ block.type }}</span>{%- endset -%}
                {%- set _blockTileBody %}
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">{{ block.summary }}</p>
                    {{ projectStatus(block.status) }}
                {% endset -%}
                {#- Click-through tile: a `.project-card` box (grid hover-lift + its own frame stripped by
                    `.project-card:has(> .fui-card)`) with an overlay `.project-card-link` anchor, NOT an
                    `<a>` wrapping the card — the proven renderProjectGrid/renderBacklogGrid pattern that
                    avoids the nested-anchor parser clone (block summaries carry no links today, but the
                    overlay pattern is the invariant). The card itself is the sole visual frame. -#}
                <div class="project-card">
                    <a href="/blocks/{{ block.id }}/" class="project-card-link" aria-label="View {{ block.name }}"></a>
                    {{ weCard(block.name, _blockTileBody, _blockTypePill, "block-tile-card") }}
                </div>
                {% endfor %}
            </div>
        </div>
        {% endif %}

        {% if intent.designSystemResearch %}
        {%- set _designResearchBody %}
            <h2>Design System Research</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-slate-600">How established design systems approach this UX concern.</p>
            <table class="data-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>System</th>
                        <th>Components</th>
                        <th>Key Insight</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for system in intent.designSystemResearch %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>{% if system.reference %}<a href="{{ system.reference }}">{{ system.system }}</a>{% else %}{{ system.system }}{% endif %}</td>
                        <td>{{ system.components | join(", ") if system.components.length else "—" }}</td>
                        <td>{{ system.keyInsight }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
        {% endset -%}
        {{ weCard("", _designResearchBody, "", "section-card mt-8") }}
        {% endif %}

        {% if intent.uxResearch %}
        {%- set _uxResearchBody %}
            <h2>UX Research</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-slate-600">Evidence-based findings on user perception and behavior.</p>

            {% for research in intent.uxResearch %}
            <div class="mb-6">
                <h3>{{ research.title }}
                    {% if research.source %}<span class="text-sm font-normal text-slate-500"> — {{ research.source }}</span>{% endif %}
                </h3>
                {% if research.findings %}
                <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 list-disc pl-5">
                    {% for finding in research.findings %}
                    <li>{{ finding }}</li>
                    {% endfor %}
                </ul>
                {% endif %}
                {% if research.reference %}
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1"><a href="{{ research.reference }}">Source</a></p>
                {% endif %}
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
        {% endset -%}
        {{ weCard("", _uxResearchBody, "", "section-card mt-8") }}
        {% endif %}

        {% if intent.researchGaps %}
        {%- set _researchGapsBody %}
            <h2>Research Gaps</h2>
            <p class="mb-4 text-slate-600">Areas where the current spec needs evolution based on research findings.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-gray-600">
                {% for gap in intent.researchGaps %}
                <li class="mb-2">{{ gap }}</li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ul>
        {% endset -%}
        {{ weCard("", _researchGapsBody, "", "section-card mt-8") }}
        {% endif %}
    </div>
</div>
